Phase 1 — Define the Business Problem (Most Important)

Before touching data, answer:

What is the goal?

Who is the stakeholder?

What decisions will be made?

Example (Retail Sales)

Identify revenue drivers

Find top-performing regions

Detect loss-making products

Analyze seasonal trends

 Deliverable: Problem Statement

 Phase 2 — Data Collection

Sources:

Kaggle datasets

Company data exports

APIs

Databases

CSV / Excel / SQL

Example:

df = pd.read_csv("superstore.csv")

 Phase 3 — Data Understanding (EDA – Exploration)

Check structure:

df.info()
df.describe()
df.head()


Understand:

column meanings

data types

missing values

duplicates

Check missing:

df.isnull().sum()


Check duplicates:

df.duplicated().sum()

 Phase 4 — Data Cleaning

Real datasets are messy — always.

Handle missing values
df.fillna(0, inplace=True)

Fix datatypes
df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])

Remove duplicates
df.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

Remove invalid values
df = df[df['Sales'] > 0]

Phase 5 — Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Trend Analysis
monthly = df.groupby('Month')['Sales'].sum()

Category Analysis
df.groupby('Category')['Sales'].sum()

Region Analysis
df.groupby('Region')['Profit'].mean()

Correlation
df.corr(numeric_only=True)

 Phase 6 — Data Visualization

Examples:

Sales Trend
sns.lineplot(x='Month', y='Sales', data=df)

Top Products
sns.barplot(x='Sales', y='Product', data=top_products)

Profit Distribution
sns.boxplot(x='Category', y='Profit', data=df)

Correlation Heatmap
sns.heatmap(df.corr(numeric_only=True), annot=True)

Phase 7 — Statistical Analysis

Examples:

Correlation Testing
stats.pearsonr(df['Discount'], df['Profit'])

Compare Regions
stats.f_oneway(
    df[df['Region']=='East']['Sales'],
    df[df['Region']=='West']['Sales']
)

Regression
sm.OLS(df['Profit'], sm.add_constant(df[['Discount']])).fit()

  Phase 8 — Generate Business Insights

Example insights:

West region generates highest revenue

High discounts reduce profit significantly

Furniture category has high loss rate

Q4 shows peak seasonal sales

 This is what hiring managers really care about.

Phase 9 — Reporting & Presentation

